{{!--
  ============================================================================
  SERVICE INSTRUCTIONS - ENGLAND SECTION 8 / FORM 3
  ============================================================================
  Canonical support document for the current England Form 3 notice workflow.
--}}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Service Instructions - {{notice_name}}</title>
  <style>
    {{{print_css}}}

    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 10mm;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0;
      color: #1a1a1a;
      font-size: 10pt;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .doc-header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 1.5em;
      padding-bottom: 1em;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #1a1a1a;
    }

    .doc-header h1 {
      margin: 0 0 0.4em 0;
      font-size: 14pt;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .doc-badge {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 0.3em 0.8em;
      background: #1a1a1a;
      color: white;
      font-size: 10pt;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .details-box,
    .callout,
    .method-card,
    .checklist-box {
      page-break-inside: avoid;
      break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .details-box,
    .checklist-box,
    .method-card {
      margin: 1.25em 0;
      border: 1px solid #d8d8d8;
      background: #fff;
    }

    .details-box,
    .checklist-box .content,
    .method-card .content {
      padding: 1em;
    }

    .details-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr;
      gap: 0.45em 1em;
    }

    .details-grid dt {
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #444;
    }

    .details-grid dd {
      margin: 0;
    }

    .callout {
      margin: 1.25em 0;
      padding: 1em;
      border-left: 4px solid #1a1a1a;
      background: #f7f7f7;
    }

    .callout.warning {
      border-color: #b45309;
      background: #fff7ed;
    }

    .callout.critical {
      border-color: #b91c1c;
      background: #fef2f2;
    }

    .section-title {
      margin: 1.75em 0 0.75em 0;
      padding-bottom: 0.4em;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #1a1a1a;
      font-size: 12pt;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .method-card .heading,
    .checklist-box .heading {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0.7em 0.9em;
      background: #1a1a1a;
      color: white;
      font-size: 11pt;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .method-card.recommended .heading {
      background: #0f172a;
    }

    ul {
      margin: 0.6em 0 0 1.2em;
    }

    li {
      margin: 0.35em 0;
    }

    .doc-footer {
      margin-top: 2em;
      padding-top: 1em;
      border-top: 1px solid #d8d8d8;
      font-size: 9pt;
      color: #555;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="doc-header">
    <h1>Service Instructions</h1>
    <span class="doc-badge">{{notice_name}}</span>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Use these instructions to serve the {{notice_name}} consistently and preserve evidence of when, where, and how service took place.</p>
    <p>This guidance is general information only. It does not replace legal advice or the need to check the tenancy agreement and the latest official guidance before serving notice.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="details-box">
    <dl class="details-grid">
      <dt>Property</dt>
      <dd>{{property_address}}</dd>
      <dt>Tenant</dt>
      <dd>{{tenant_full_name}}{{#if tenant_2_name}}, {{tenant_2_name}}{{/if}}</dd>
      <dt>Notice</dt>
      <dd>{{notice_name}}</dd>
      {{#if (hasValue service_date_formatted)}}
      <dt>Notice service date</dt>
      <dd>{{service_date_formatted}}</dd>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if (hasValue notice_expiry_date_formatted)}}
      <dt>Notice expiry date</dt>
      <dd>{{notice_expiry_date_formatted}}</dd>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if (hasValue earliest_proceedings_date_formatted)}}
      <dt>Earliest proceedings date</dt>
      <dd>{{earliest_proceedings_date_formatted}}</dd>
      {{/if}}
    </dl>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-title">Recommended Service Method</h2>

  {{#if (eq service_method "post")}}
  <div class="method-card">
    <div class="heading">First Class Post</div>
    <div class="content">
      <ul>
        <li>Send the {{notice_name}} by Royal Mail first class post.</li>
        <li>Keep the proof of posting receipt and a copy of the notice served.</li>
        <li>Record the date of posting and keep any follow-up correspondence.</li>
        <li>Use the service date and proceedings date shown above as your canonical pack timeline.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  {{else if (eq service_method "recorded_delivery")}}
  <div class="method-card">
    <div class="heading">Recorded or Signed Delivery</div>
    <div class="content">
      <ul>
        <li>Keep the tracking reference and delivery outcome.</li>
        <li>Be cautious: a refused or uncollected item can create service disputes.</li>
        <li>Keep a backup plan ready if there is any doubt about receipt.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  {{else}}
  <div class="method-card recommended">
    <div class="heading">Hand Delivery</div>
    <div class="content">
      <ul>
        <li>Deliver the {{notice_name}} through the letterbox or directly to the tenant if appropriate.</li>
        <li>Record the date and exact time of service immediately.</li>
        <li>If possible, take a witness and a contemporaneous photograph of delivery.</li>
        <li>Keep the served copy with your pack evidence.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  {{/if}}

  <div class="callout warning">
    <p><strong>Electronic service:</strong> Do not rely on email or text alone unless the tenancy terms clearly permit electronic service and you are satisfied the clause applies to notices of this kind.</p>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-title">Evidence To Keep</h2>

  <div class="checklist-box">
    <div class="heading">Service Evidence Checklist</div>
    <div class="content">
      <ul>
        <li>A copy of the completed {{notice_name}} that was served.</li>
        <li>Proof of posting, tracking, or witness details, depending on the service method used.</li>
        <li>A contemporaneous note of the service date, time, location, and method.</li>
        <li>Any tenant acknowledgement or later correspondence that refers to receipt of the notice.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-title">After Service</h2>

  <div class="checklist-box">
    <div class="heading">Next Steps</div>
    <div class="content">
      <ul>
        {{#if (hasValue notice_expiry_date_formatted)}}
        <li>Allow the notice period to run until {{notice_expiry_date_formatted}}.</li>
        {{/if}}
        {{#if (hasValue earliest_proceedings_date_formatted)}}
        <li>Do not start possession proceedings before {{earliest_proceedings_date_formatted}}.</li>
        {{/if}}
        <li>Do not change locks, remove belongings, or try to force the tenant out without a court order and lawful enforcement.</li>
        <li>If the tenant remains, the standard court route is usually Form N5 with Form N119. Some rent-arrears-only claims may also be suitable for PCOL.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout critical">
    <p><strong>Important:</strong> Incorrect service or weak service evidence can delay or undermine the possession claim even where the factual grounds are otherwise strong.</p>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-title">Common Mistakes To Avoid</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Using a notice timeline in one document that does not match the rest of the pack.</li>
    <li>Leaving the service method undocumented.</li>
    <li>Serving by a method that the tenancy does not allow without checking the consequences.</li>
    <li>Starting proceedings before the earliest proceedings date has passed.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="doc-footer">
    <p><strong>Generated:</strong> {{generated_date}}</p>
    {{#unless clean_output}}
    <p><strong>Landlord Heaven</strong> | England Section 8 support document</p>
    {{/unless}}
  </div>
</body>
</html>
